sentence: Looking at options trading activity among components of the S&P 500 index, there is noteworthy activity today in Wynn Resorts Ltd (Symbol: WYNN), where a total volume of 32,392 contracts has been traded thus far today, a contract volume which is representative of approximately 3.2 million underlying shares (given that every 1 contract represents 100 underlying shares).
That number works out to 131.3% of WYNN's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 2.5 million shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $126 strike call option expiring May 12, 2017 , with 1,933 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 193,300 underlying shares of WYNN.

Alphabet Inc (Symbol: GOOG) saw options trading volume of 18,328 contracts, representing approximately 1.8 million underlying shares or approximately 125.8% of GOOG's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 1.5 million shares.
Particularly high volume was seen for the $932.50 strike call option expiring May 12, 2017 , with 2,325 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 232,500 underlying shares of GOOG.

Particularly high volume was seen for the $162.50 strike call option expiring May 19, 2017 , with 7,134 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 713,400 underlying shares of HD.
